<h3 class="mb-3 mt-5">What Are Cookies?</h3>
<p>Cookies are small data files stored on your device when you visit a website. They save information about your activity to help websites remember your preferences and provide a better user experience.</p>
<p>Cookies serve various functions, such as storing login credentials, language settings, and other preferences. They also enable essential website operations and provide insights into user interactions, allowing us to refine our services.</p>
<p>Cookies may be placed by the website you visit (first-party cookies) or by third-party services we use for analytics, content delivery, and advertising. These third-party cookies help track usage patterns across different websites to provide personalized advertisements and analyze behavior.</p>
<p>For more details on cookies, visit www.aboutcookies.org or www.allaboutcookies.org.</p>

